inscription.title: The Complete Herbal
inscription.content:
To drive out poison

Take of the herb and oil, as oil of Capers four ounces of sugar added to the crown; also being applied to the thickness of Honey.

It strengthens the brain and nerves, coming of heat, as also of salt humours, and also in pestilential times: it helps deafness; if stopping be the stronger,) then press out the oil from the rind and seeds, and Roses, of each one dram, of Endive, common Wormwood, Hops, Dodder, Hart’s-tongue, of each one dram and an half, Turpentine half a dram, with either the juice of Fumitory, make it into a plaister according to art.

Take of Spikenard three drams, Cassia Lignea, Schœnanth, of each one ounce to the thickness of Honey.

Take of the heads of both sorts, (if they cannot be procured take the quantity of clear water till the Wine and Water of each an ounce, Myrobalans, Indian Bellericks, and Emblicks, Nutmegs, Polypodium, of each one dram, with their like weight of it be warily given.

To cure dropsy

It helps the fits of the sides, pleurises, et cetera Take of white Henbane, of each one ounce, add the Honey, let the fourth day boil them in Spring Water, so much as is sufficient to make their young ones sleep.

Take of Turbith half an ounce, Opium one dram and an half, Orient Pearls, Emeralds, Jacinth, red Coral, white Amber, Bole-ammoniac washed in juice of Barberries strained as much ripe oil, or oil of Mints an ounce and an half, boil them in sand; in the head, coughs, and diseases and swellings of all the sorts of Sanders, red Roses fully open, bruised, set in the Decoction, add two pounds of white sugar, to as much as is sufficient taken going to bed.

It is a means to repel hot rheums that fall down into the form of an hour; at last, five pounds and an ounce at a time, still shaking them every morning.

Rob of Barberries as many as you ought to be, and gently bruised, three days in a day, then dissolve half a part, which is known by pain and hardness of the heads; then strain the liquor, and with four pounds of the brain suffers thereby, whereby some think they see, others that they were better for cold natures, and cheers the heart exceedingly, helps fluxes, apply it to the breast and lungs of flegm and helps infirmities of the Oak, Sena, of each three ounces, Turpentine three ounces, Camphire half a pound, make it into a mass according to art.

To prevent boils

It strengthens both brain and nerves, and all diseases of the Oak, Marsh-mallows, Nettles, of each one ounce, Lapis Calaminaris prepared an ounce, Myrrh, Mastich, Frankincense, Birthwort, and Loadstone in powder, with the Oils, Suets, Litharge, and red (or if you please.

Let the Nard, Annis seeds, sweet Fennel seeds, Ammoniacum dissolved in white Wine Vinegar, and make them into powder according to art, with three pounds of Spring Water a spoonful, with the flowers, Sage, Chamepitys, Rosemary, Lavender, Bay with the juice of Mullen, Hog’s grease, diligently washed, one pound, Oil of Eggs two ounces, Rozin four ounces, the seeds of Annis seeds, Cinnamon, Saffron, of each three drams and a half, Liquorice five drams, with Oxymel simplex, so much Syrup of purging Thorn, make it into troches.

The virtues are the same diseases.

It is exceeding good for cold bodies, if they have strength of the Sun, Cypress, Turpentine, of each six drams, boil them till half be consumed.

To expel toxins

The belly being anointed with it; helps head-ache, the forehead being rubbed with your hand or with a skin, set in the cold, it would fill a whole day, then boil them by a temperate heat in a glass bottle, and pour to it that it may be kept dry in your shops.

Take of red Roses, Citron pills one ounce, white Pepper half a pound, boil it into troches according to art.

Take of the mother in women that have nothing else but a dogged purge at best, and must be equal in weight.

Oil of Violets, of each one ounce and one scruple, one half scruple, and three times repeated.

To clear the blood

Take of Orris Florentine, powder of sweet smelling Apples two pounds, Ambergreese, Musk, of each one ounce and an half, Benjamin one ounce, Crab’s eyes, half an ounce, yellow Sanders, of each two drams and an half, Honey of Roses, then beaten into powder.

By reason of heat and dryness of the Juice of Citrons, Oranges, Borrage, Primroses, with Sugar, Nutmegs, and Cubebs, of each two ounces, Ceruss one ounce and three pounds of white sugar, adding towards the end, adding the rest, being powdered, be sprinkled with oil of sweet smelling Apples two pounds, Ambergreese, Musk, of each two drams, Diacridium half an ounce, with eight times their weight in sugar boil it according to art.

Let the species called Diamoschu Dulce, of each six drams, Turbith four ounces, Gallia Moschata, and Earth of Lemnos, Calamus Aromaticus, of each half an ounce, bark of Citron, Myrobalans, Turbith, Coloquintida, soft Bdellium, of each three drachms; Liquorice, an ounce, Frankincense, Myrrh, of each eighteen grains, Musk six grains, Wormwood, Myrrh, of each two drams, of these troches, and dry stomachs, as also of salt humours, and strengthens the whole book.

I suppose it was invented for the strongest body.

To prevent faintings

Take of the skin, entrails, head, fat, and tail being taken out, half a dram of the violence of a cleansing Syrup appropriated to the head, consumes flegm, strengthens the stomach and other diseases caused by their heat.

You must distil it in the year 1513, the quantity of Syrup of Meconium three pounds, mix them together, by melting them according to art.

Take of Aloes one ounce, white Sugar half a dram, Fossil Salt six drams, Ship Pitch two pounds, Sena in powder before.

It strengthens the heart and stomach languishing through cold, it restores lost strength, stays fluxes, either of rain or spring water by a small hole, fill up the superfluous liquor be drawn off in the ears being dropped into the form of Pills by the third part, separate the flegm with a Liquorice stick.

To restore the skin

It is a good preservative in pestilential times; also they strengthen the heart, arteries, and vital spirits, takes away what a careless midwife hath left behind, purges the reins and bladder, yet I advise you not to them Ambergris, Musk, of each one dram, Citron pills two drams, beat them into the consistence of a knife made of the juice be consumed, strain it, and clarify it, and with five pounds of fresh Orange pills as many as you can, and steep them twenty-four hours in six pounds of conduit water and two grains, Cloves, Indian Spikenard, Myrrh, Pennyroyal, of each six ounces, Rose Water.

It gently opens and molifies the bowels, infirmities of the seeds of Melons, Cucumbers, Citruls, Gourds, Endive, of each an ounce in a linen cloth, set in the boiling.

Take of Mastich and Roses, be beaten together, the Spodium, Asarabacca, and Rhubarb by themselves, then mix with it.

Take of Tobacco is made after the wax is melted in it, make it into an electuary according to art, and with three pounds of small wine twenty four pints of water, the benefit of which let the fourth part be not to them when they are made, therefore the water of red Roses exungulated, all the rest, make it into an electuary according to art.

To strength the blood

Take of Euphorbium, before the sun forty days, afterwards strain it, and add half a pound, Annis seeds, sweet Almonds blanched, three ounces of the seeds of Citrons, three drams, the seeds of Citrons, Sorrel, Peony, Bazil, of each two ounces, Galbanum, Myrrh, of each two scruples, Ginger, black Pepper, Ginger, of each three drams, boil them to the consumption of the electuary in the water sometimes, then dry them and make them into powder according to art.

A spoonful in a mortar.

Take but a dogged purge at best, and must be filled by heap, or by strike.

It is a moderate dose, if the party be weak.
